						               													<description>In Chicken Hunter, players simultaneously reveal cards from their hand, aiming to score points.   There are no restrictions on what cards players can reveal (e.g. does not need to be a straight, or x-of-a-kind).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In each round, two hands will be rewarded with points.  First, look at the players who revealed the fewest number of cards.  This player earns points equal to the number of cards they revealed multiplied by the sum of the face value of these cards.  (In the case of a tie, the tied players first discard one card each.)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Then, from the remaining players, look at the player with the lowest face value sum of the cards revealed.  This player scores points using the same calculation.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Afterwards, players draw up to 6 cards and repeat the process.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game lasts until a player achieves a preset threshold and at that point the person with the most points wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
